# Claude Agent SDK

Build autonomous agents that can understand code, edit files, run commands, and complete complex tasks.

## Installation

```bash
npm install @anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk
```

Requires Node.js 18+ and an `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` environment variable.

## Quick Start

```typescript
import { ClaudeAgent } from "@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk";

const agent = new ClaudeAgent({
  model: "claude-sonnet-4-6",
  apiKey: process.env.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY,
});

// Send a task and stream the response
const stream = agent.message({
  message: "Read the package.json and explain what this project does",
  workingDirectory: "/path/to/project",
});

for await (const event of stream) {
  if (event.type === "text") {
    process.stdout.write(event.text);
  } else if (event.type === "tool_use") {
    console.log(`Using tool: ${event.tool}`);
  }
}
```

## Core Concepts

### Agent Sessions

An agent session maintains conversation context across multiple interactions:

```typescript
const agent = new ClaudeAgent({
  model: "claude-sonnet-4-6",
  systemPrompt: "You are a senior developer. Write clean, well-tested code.",
  tools: ["bash", "text_editor", "file_reader"],
});

// First message
await agent.message({ message: "Create a new Express API with health endpoint" });

// Follow-up (conversation context is preserved)
await agent.message({ message: "Add rate limiting middleware" });
```

### Tool Permissions

Control which tools the agent can use and which operations require approval:

```typescript
const agent = new ClaudeAgent({
  model: "claude-sonnet-4-6",
  permissions: {
    bash: { autoApprove: ["ls", "cat", "grep", "find"] },
    fileWrite: { autoApprove: ["src/**/*.ts", "tests/**/*.ts"] },
    fileRead: { autoApprove: true },
  },
});
```

### Streaming Events

The SDK streams events as the agent works:

```typescript
const stream = agent.message({ message: "Fix the failing test" });

for await (const event of stream) {
  switch (event.type) {
    case "text":
      // Claude's text output
      process.stdout.write(event.text);
      break;
    case "tool_use":
      // Tool being called (bash, file edit, etc.)
      console.log(`Tool: ${event.tool} - ${event.description}`);
      break;
    case "tool_result":
      // Result from tool execution
      console.log(`Result: ${event.output}`);
      break;
    case "error":
      console.error(`Error: ${event.message}`);
      break;
  }
}
```

### Custom Tools

Extend the agent with custom tools using the [[anthropic/tool-use]] format:

```typescript
const agent = new ClaudeAgent({
  model: "claude-sonnet-4-6",
  customTools: [
    {
      name: "run_tests",
      description: "Run the project test suite and return results",
      input_schema: {
        type: "object",
        properties: {
          pattern: { type: "string", description: "Test file pattern" }
        }
      },
      handler: async (input) => {
        // Your test runner logic
        const result = await runTests(input.pattern);
        return { output: result };
      }
    }
  ]
});
```

## Built-in Tools

| Tool | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `bash` | Execute shell commands |
| `text_editor` | View and edit files |
| `file_reader` | Read file contents |
| `web_search` | Search the web |
| `web_fetch` | Fetch web page content |

## Configuration Options

```typescript
new ClaudeAgent({
  model: string,              // Model ID (required)
  apiKey: string,             // API key (default: ANTHROPIC_API_KEY env)
  systemPrompt: string,       // Custom system instructions
  workingDirectory: string,   // Default working directory
  tools: string[],            // Built-in tools to enable
  customTools: Tool[],        // Custom tool definitions
  permissions: Permissions,   // Tool permission configuration
  maxTokens: number,          // Max output tokens per turn
  maxTurns: number,           // Max agentic loop iterations
});
```

## Use Cases

- **Code generation** — Generate features from natural language descriptions
- **Bug fixing** — Analyze errors, locate bugs, and apply fixes
- **Code review** — Review PRs and suggest improvements
- **Refactoring** — Restructure code while maintaining behavior
- **Testing** — Write and run tests for existing code
- **Documentation** — Generate docs from code
- **DevOps** — Manage deployments, debug infrastructure

## Comparison with Messages API

| Feature | Messages API | Agent SDK |
|---------|-------------|----------|
| Conversation management | Manual | Automatic |
| Tool execution | Your code | SDK handles it |
| File system access | Not built-in | Built-in |
| Shell execution | Not built-in | Built-in |
| Streaming | SSE events | Typed event stream |
| Multi-turn loops | Manual | Automatic |

Use the Messages API ([[anthropic/messages]]) when you need full control. Use the Agent SDK when you want batteries-included agent behavior.

## Environment Variables

| Variable | Purpose |
|----------|----------|
| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | API key (required) |
| `ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL` | Override API endpoint |

scripts.inline:
import { ClaudeAgent } from "@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk";

const agent = new ClaudeAgent({
  model: process.env.ANTHROPIC_MODEL || "claude-sonnet-4-6",
  systemPrompt: "You are a helpful coding assistant. Be concise and write clean code.",
  tools: ["bash", "text_editor", "file_reader"],
  permissions: {
    fileRead: { autoApprove: true },
    bash: { autoApprove: ["ls", "cat", "grep", "find", "echo", "pwd"] },
  },
});

const task = process.argv[2] || "List the files in the current directory and describe the project structure";

console.log(`Task: ${task}\n---`);

const stream = agent.message({
  message: task,
  workingDirectory: process.cwd(),
});

for await (const event of stream) {
  if (event.type === "text") {
    process.stdout.write(event.text);
  } else if (event.type === "tool_use") {
    console.log(`\n[Tool: ${event.tool}]`);
  }
}

console.log("\n--- Done");
